reviewText: Since this IS a "Maneater" SyFy-Channel movie, it has a few things you'd EXPECT:=====> Blood.=====> Guts.=====> Reasonably priced=====> At least ONE famous singer/TV/movie star appears.=====> Under 91-minutes.---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------I bought this andGargoyle - Wings of Darknessand put them in a clear double-DVD case with one liner facing in, and the other, out.While neither movie will ever be on anyone's TOP TEN list of all-time greats, theywere BOTH enjoyable... TO ME!
summary: I happen to LOVE all of the "maneater" series.
Title: Rise of the Gargoyles: Maneater Series

reviewText: Don't believe the hype on here, this is just another b grade film that should have been made with a bigger budget, makes you crave for the 70's Gargoyles film that Stan Winston did the effects on, at least that was scary and well made.So may I suggest you buy that film instead, don't waste your time or money on this one.
Title: Rise of the Gargoyles: Maneater Series

reviewText: Much like Carny, this movie tries to do something different than average Syfy-commissioned films. There's less creature attacks, lower body count (less characters period), and considerably more focus on mystery and such, even though the audience already knows what's going on.Among the very few Syfy-commissioned films that tries to be spooky.One question though: does France even have churches.
summary: Can I rate four for effort?
Title: Rise of the Gargoyles: Maneater Series

reviewText: Saw a while ago, from about halfway through, and always wondered how it started.  Was so glad I found this.  I love Gargoyles, even though movies always depict them as evil creatures, not protectors.

reviewText: I purchased this DVD as a joke for a sister that loves Eric Balfour. It's a "b" movie with some surprizes. Eric is fun to watch, and has a good time with it.
Title: Rise of the Gargoyles: Maneater Series

reviewText: The first Gargoyles movie I saw was made int he 60s and starred Cornel Wilde and Jennifer Salt. The movie was intelligent, well acted, and had great special effects for the time. This movie looks at Gargoyles in a similar way, but the creatures are more violent, bloody, and nasty. The special effects are, of course, better but CGI helps with that. I enjoyed the movie the coupld of times I saw it on the SciFi channel. TV is so bad these days, I find myself preferring my DVD collection.
